    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-05-05T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-05-05T13:00:00-05:00" n="294"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d294">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.84/75a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-05T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 5, 1936—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>148. Your 249, May 5, 5 p.m.<note n="29" xml:id="d294fn29">Not printed.</note>
                    and earlier telegrams. Please express to the Foreign Office and through it to
                    Sir Sidney Barton our sincere appreciation for the prompt and effective
                    assistance rendered in the evacuation of the American Legation at Addis
                        Ababa.<note n="30" xml:id="d294fn30">For the official British account of
                        these disturbances, see British Cmd. 5213, Ethiopia No. 5 (1936): <hi
                            rend="italic">Reports and Correspondence Regarding the Rescue and Relief
                            of British and Foreign Nationals at Addis Ababa During the Disturbances
                            of May 2–6, 1936</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Please endeavor to keep us promptly advised of developments at Addis Ababa. In
                    this connection we hope it will be possible for Barton to transmit to us through
                    Foreign Office and your Embassy brief reports from Engert from time to time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
